# typography / metafont

METAFONT is Donald Knuth's parametric font-description language: a `.mf` program defines glyphs as pen-stroke paths and filled regions driven by equations (stroke width, slant, x-height, serif size). Changing parameters yields a whole family from one source. The `mf` engine rasterizes the source to a GF bitmap + TFM metrics; we render a proof sheet to a PNG image.

controls do
