end

## Required reading
- The METAFONTbook / mf(1) man page — https://www.mankier.com/1/mf (official, TeX Live docs / Donald E. Knuth)
- Metafont overview (GF/TFM output, pen model) — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metafont (CC BY-SA, Wikipedia contributors)
- mf2pt1 manual — Metafont source to PostScript Type 1 — https://www.ctan.org/pkg/mf2pt1 (LPPL, Scott Pakin / Werner Lemberg)
- METAFONT for Beginners (tutorial PDF) — http://ftp.cvut.cz/tex-archive/info/metafont/beginners/metafont-for-beginners.pdf (free doc, Christophe Grandsire et al.)
- GitHub topic: metafont — https://github.com/topics/metafont (community examples)

## Render
```bash
# install (macOS) — adds mf-nowin, gftodvi, dvipng to PATH
brew install --cask mactex-no-gui

# rasterize source to GF bitmap + TFM metrics
mf-nowin '\mode=localfont; mode_setup; mag=4; nonstopmode; input font'

# render a proof sheet to PNG
gftodvi font.*gf && dvipng -D150 -o font-proof.png font.dvi
```

## Failure modes
- `mf` only finds `font.mf` if it is in the current dir or TEXINPUTS — run from the source dir or set the path.
- Output filename is `jobname.<dpi>gf`; the dpi depends on `mode` × `mag`, so glob `font.*gf` rather than hardcoding a dpi.
- `\mode=proof` produces large proof rasters; use `localfont` for normal dpi. Wrong/unknown mode aborts with `! Unknown mode`.
- Without `nonstopmode` the engine drops into an interactive `*` prompt and hangs in headless runs.
- GF is a bitmap — there is no direct vector/PNG output from `mf`; you must pipe through `gftodvi` + `dvipng` (or use `mf2pt1` for Type 1 outlines).
- `mf2pt1` requires every glyph drawn from closed fill/unfill paths; pen-stroked-only glyphs fail to convert.
